headline: Where Will Palantir Stock Be in 1 Year?
summary: Few companies have reacted more to Trump's presidential election victory than Palantir Technologies (NYSE: PLTR), a data analytics and artificial intelligence (AI) company with a strong focus on defense and law enforcement.  The company has added billions to its market cap, with shares up by a jaw-dropping 50% since the election.  Founded in 2003, Palantir is arguably an early AI company.

headline: Palantir Stock Is Having a Bad Day. It’s Still Having a Terrific Year.
summary: Shares of  Palantir Technologies  were trading lower Monday, but stock of the software company still boasts incredible gains this year.  The software stock fell 7.4% to $60.90 in afternoon trading and was on track for its largest daily percentage decrease since July, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  Last week, the company said that it will transfer its stock to the Nasdaq Global Select Market, switching from the New York Stock Exchange on Nov. 26.

headline: Why Palantir Stock Was Pulling Back Today
summary: After a dramatic bull run in recent weeks, Palantir Technologies (NYSE: PLTR) stock was finally giving up gains, as investors seemed to be taking profits after Friday's pop.  Palantir stock was down 5.38% as of 11:45 a.m. ET.  A pullback in Palantir stock seemed inevitable after it had jumped more than 50% since its earnings report on Nov. 4, lifting its price-to-sales ratio above 50.
